  "text": "The columns for sequence length (m) and point matching tolerance (r) parameters were relatively consistent across studies. The most common parameter settings for sequence length was m = 2. The most common setting for the point matching tolerance was r = 0.15. Of note, a couple studies explicitly evaluated multiple ranges for these parameters [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
